comment_data.body:
I can reproduce this issue.

I filed https://github.com/dart-lang/sdk/issues/36972 for the analysis server team.

Actually, I'm not sure I reproduced this exact issue. It looks like it might be a version incompatibility. I think the beta channel includes a Dart SDK that is incompatible with the latest Dart plugin. You could try switching Flutter to the dev channel. Or you can go to the Dart plugin page in the Jetbrains repository and download an older one then install it from disk.

If you decide to try either, please let us know how it goes.

I tried below,

1. Switch beta channel to dev channel -> no effect ðŸ˜• 
2. Re `git clone` project source codes -> Error popup disappears, language server runs ðŸ™Œ 

After that, I found some symlinks in `ios` directory caused this error.
Our project has some project-oriented plugins in project directory.

```
(project root)
| -- android/
| -- lib/
| -- ios/
| -- plugins/
        | -- foo/
        |       | -- example/
        |       |        | -- ios/
        |       |        |        | -- .symlinks/
        |       |        |        |        | -- plugins/
        |       |        |        |        |        | -- @ foo        <- I removed files like this
        | -- bar
```

Symlink file in plugin's example make a cycle.
Maybe it causes the error, I think.

@kikuchy Thanks for the update!

@bwilkerson Are you aware of any issues with symlinks?
@stereotype441 Maybe I should ask you: are you aware of any issues with symlinks?
